The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 March is 40,508 (4,688.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 March, there were 424 new confirmed cases (49.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 February, there were 743 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 43% (319 fewer cases).
